      <title>Van Power Upgrade Mistakes: The Wrong Fix Patterns (and What to Do Instead)</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/van-power-upgrade-mistakes/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 22 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/van-power-upgrade-mistakes/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Upgrades should be deliberate, not panic buttons. The pattern that usually works is simple:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Fix leaks → protect baseline → improve recovery speed → then add capacity.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Start here:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/van-power-upgrade-checklist/&#34; &gt;Van Power Upgrade Checklist&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/van-power-upgrade-paths/&#34; &gt;Van Power Upgrade Paths&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Mistake 1 — Buying more Wh instead of improving recovery speed&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;mistake-1--buying-more-wh-instead-of-improving-recovery-speed&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;span&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#mistake-1--buying-more-wh-instead-of-improving-recovery-speed&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Pattern:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
